\b\fs40 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sb240\qj
\cf0 Resumo\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb60\qj

\b0\fs24 \cf0 Usu\'e1rios de m\'e9todos \'e1geis e comunidade de software livre compartilham culturas similares mas com diferentes abordagens para superar dificuldades. Apesar dos diversos profissionais envolvidos em ambos mundos, os m\'e9todos \'e1geis n\'e3o s\'e3o t\'e3o fortes quanto poderiam na comunidade de software livre nem o contr\'e1rio. Esse trabalho identifica e exp\'f5e os obst\'e1culos que separam essas comunidade. Com ele, espera-se extrair as melhores solu\'e7\'f5es de cada comunidade e contribuir com sugest\'f5es de ferramenta e processos de desenvolvimento em ambos ambientes.\

\b Palavras-chave:
\b0  m\'e9todos \'e1geis, open source, software livre\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb240\sa60\ql\qnatural

\b\fs40 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sb240\qj
\cf0 Abstract\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb60\qj

\b0\fs24 \cf0 Agile methods and open source software communities share similar cultures with different approaches to overcome problems. Although several professionals are involved in both worlds, neither agile methodologies are as strong as they could be in open source communities nor those communities provide strong contributions to agile methods. This work identifies and exposes the obstacles that separate those communities in order to extract the best of them and improve both sides with suggestions of tools and development processes.\

\b Keywords:
\b0  agile methods, open source\
\pard\pardeftab720\sb240\sa60\ql\qnatural

